description:
Yebo Cao discovered that Python incorrectly handled certain URLs.
An attacker could use this issue to bypass blockinglisting methods.
This issue was first addressed in USN-5960-1, but was incomplete.
Here we address an additional fix to that issue. (CVE-2023-24329)
title: Python vulnerability
summary: python2.7, python3.10, python3.11, python3.5, python3.6, python3.8 vulnerability
action: In general, a standard system update will make all the necessary changes.
isummary: Python could be made to bypass blocklisting methods if a specially crafted URL was provided
